If we want to build public support for socialism we must make foreign policy part of our analysis.
Foreign Policy for American Capitalists Ever since the 1930s the US government has pushed for trade agreements that give American companies access to foreign markets.
Ties between the United States and foreign militaries are further cemented through arms sales since purchasers remain dependent on the United States for training and intelligence.
